### Installation

1.  **Clone the repository:**
    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/your-username/{{.ProjectName}}.git
    cd {{.ProjectName}}
    ```

2.  **Set up environment variables:**
    ```bash
    cp .env.example .env
    ```
    *Update the `.env` file with your configuration, especially database credentials.*

3.  **Install dependencies:**
    ```bash
    go mod tidy
    ```

{{- if .Database}}

4.  **Database Setup:**

    {{if eq .Tool.String "gorm"}}
    *Ensure your database server is running and the credentials in `.env` are correct, then run the migrations:*
    ```bash
    make migrate
    ```
    {{else if eq .Tool.String "sqlc"}}
    *This project uses **sqlc** to generate type-safe Go code from your SQL queries. After modifying any `.sql` files in the `storage/queries` directory, you must regenerate the code:*
    ```bash
    make sqlc-generate
    ```
    **Note on Migrations:** For `sqlc`, migrations are not handled automatically. You are responsible for managing database schema changes. We recommend using a tool like [golang-migrate/migrate](https://github.com/golang-migrate/migrate).
    {{else if eq .Tool.String "sqlx"}}
    **Note on Migrations:** For `sqlx`, migrations are not handled automatically. You are responsible for managing database schema changes. We recommend using a tool like [golang-migrate/migrate](https://github.com/golang-migrate/migrate).
    {{end}}
{{- end}}

5.  **Run the application:**
    ```bash
    make dev
    ```
    The server will start on `http://localhost:8080` (or the port specified in `.env`).

